2. This Certificate is issued based on provisional books of accounts provided to us by promoters till 30.11.2020
3.  In Annexure to CA Certificate (Form 3A), in the column "Date of Agreement of Sale",  date of Agreement of sale or Date of Sale deed as applicable in particular case is provided.
4.  In Annexure to CA Certificate (Form 3A), some units are booked where payment more than 10% has been receive, however Agreement to sale has not been executed. The management have given explanation that, allottee has given written request to Promotor that allottee is not sure about in whose name document to be executed, so till the name is  finalized do not execute the agreement to sale.
5.  In Annexure to CA Certificate (Form 3A), in the column"Mobile Number of Allottee" as per request of promoters, contact number of Promotor is provided due to security reasons.

physProgressList.reason: Architect and engineer certificate is issued based on physical verification of construction, which CA Certificate is issued based on the verification of books of accounts.

Secondly, engineer certificate does not consider land cost  while in  CA Certificate land cost as well as construciton cost is included. Another difference is due to cost incurred is considered in Engineer Certificate and cost incurred and paid is considered in CA Certificate. So percentage completion shall be different in both certificates.
